%% Ciclo de vida de modelos: captura, edge (inferencia + feedback), drift, reentrenamiento y OTA
%% Clases L (hub), E (hub int8), H (host, tiempo real), W (worker batch/offline)
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant MI as Plantillas
    participant CI as Cintura (hub)
    participant HO as Host (laptop/celular)
    participant WK as Worker (laptop/nube)
    participant SB as Supabase (DB + storage)

    Note over MI,CI: Plantillas calculan features por-pie (ambos modos); la cintura fusiona

    rect rgb(238,243,255)
    Note over CI,SB: MODO CAPTURA (construccion de dataset)
    MI->>MI: muestreo 100 Hz + features por-pie + eventos
    MI->>CI: crudo continuo + features por-pie + eventos (WiFi)
    CI->>CI: fusion bilateral (simetria, double support)
    CI->>HO: crudo + features (BLE)
    HO->>SB: guardar crudo (Parquet) + features (DB)
    end

    rect rgb(238,252,243)
    Note over MI,SB: MODO EDGE (uso real)
    MI->>MI: muestreo 100 Hz + features por-pie + eventos
    MI->>CI: features por-pie + eventos (WiFi)
    CI->>CI: fusion bilateral + inferencia clase L (hub)
    opt modelo clase H (no entra en la cintura)
        CI->>HO: features -> host infiere en tiempo real
        HO-->>CI: score
    end
    CI-->>MI: feedback vibrotactil si hay anomalia
    CI->>HO: features + scores (BLE notif)
    HO->>SB: persistir features/scores (DB)
    Note over MI: buffer circular de crudo por-pie
    CI->>MI: pedir snippet (anomalia)
    MI->>CI: snippet de crudo
    CI->>HO: snippet -> storage
    HO->>SB: guardar snippet (storage)
    end

    rect rgb(255,247,238)
    Note over CI,WK: DRIFT -> REENTRENAMIENTO (clases E/H/W ; nunca RT en el worker)
    CI->>HO: flag de drift (Mahalanobis = sensor de drift)
    HO->>SB: registrar drift + encolar retrain_job
    SB->>WK: job (drift/schedule/manual) + datos
    WK->>WK: reentrenar (E/H: pesos int8 ; W: batch/analisis)
    WK->>SB: subir artefacto + version + metricas (registry)
    SB->>HO: nuevo modelo disponible
    HO->>CI: OTA A/B (pesos/firmware) + checksum
    CI->>CI: validar, conmutar slot, last-known-good
    alt modelo nuevo OK
        CI->>HO: ACK version activa
        HO->>SB: marcar deployment activo
    else fallo / mal desempeno
        CI->>CI: rollback a last-known-good
        CI->>HO: reportar rollback
    end
    end
